```suggestion
@[simp] lemma δ_units_smul (k : Rˣ) (z : Cochain F G n) : δ n m (k • z) = k • δ n m z :=
  δ_smul .. 
```

This declaration is a bit slow, but it's slow with or with the `simp only`
```suggestion
    simp
```
Personally I find the original cleaner. Do you have a reason to prefer the explicit `rw`?

Mostly just that it relies on the exact definition of the `Ixx`es. `rw` should be robust to changes there (though I suppose those are unlikely), but might also give a better error message if `filter_upwards` ends up creating a different goal here (which may be equally unlikely). Happy to revert these parts if you'd like
I think the old version is supposed to get a `deprecated` tag now. Please add an inline comment with "deprecated on <current-date>"

```suggestion
  .mk (b.linearIndependent.of_isLocalizedModule Rₛ S f) <| by
    rw [Set.range_comp, span_eq_top_of_isLocalizedModule Rₛ S _ b.span_eq]
```
